Zero Programmer's Calculator
----------------------------

Ideas
-----
- assembly console (utilise wpm assembler)

Button Bars
-----------

Top Bar
-------

- zero menu item is for techniques such as those in <zero/trix.h>

-----------------------------------------
| menu	| func	| stack | setup	| misc	|
-----------------------------------------
    |	    |	    |	    |	    |
-----------------------------------------
| eval  | log   | swap  | base  | rand  |
-----------------------------------------
| load  | exp   | drop  | size  | fract |
-----------------------------------------
| exec  | trig  |	| type  | zero  |
-----------------	-----------------
| save	| vector|
-----------------
| expr	| matrix|
-----------------
| equ   | cmplx |
-----------------

menu
----

Display
--------

		toggle ------	    ---	toggle
			    |       |
-----------------------------------------
| 0x00000001		|  HEX	|  U32	|	- unsigned 32-bit value
-----------------------------------------
| 0x00000000.00000000	|  HEX	|  F64	|	- 64-bit floating point value
-----------------------------------------
| 0x0000.0000		|  HEX	|  F32	|	- 32-bit floating point value
-----------------------------------------
| -0xffff		|  HEX	|  S16	|	- signed 16-bit value
-----------------------------------------
| -123456		|  DEC	|  S32	|	- signed 32-bit value in decimal
-----------------------------------------
|			|  HEX  |  S32	|	- input field
-----------------------------------------
			    |	    |
			    ----------- current modes
Operation Pad
-------------

-------------------------------------------------
|   d	|   e	|   f	|   ~	|   ++	|   --	|
-------------------------------------------------
|   a	|   b	|   c	|   %	|   >>	|   E	|
-----------------------------------------	|
|   7	|   8	|   9	|   /	|   <<	|   N	|
-----------------------------------------	|
|   4	|   5	|   6	|   *	|   ^	|   T	|
-----------------------------------------	|
|   1	|   2	|   3	|   -	|   |	|   E	|
-----------------------------------------	|
|   0  	|   .	| SPACE	|   +	|   &	|   R	|
-------------------------------------------------

Debug Pad
---------
- registers (%r0 through %r15)
- variable assignments
- debug console

